<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fire histories are sparse or lacking for California. Elsewhere, stands burn when dry, especially those occupying bottomlands with heavy fuel loads. <i>Artemisia cana </i>survives surface fires, even severe ones that top-kill. It has the strongest sprouting response of any woody sagebrush to fire. It sprouts from root crowns, rhizomes, and roots; it readily colonizes burned areas by seed from nearby unburned plants (Howard 2002a).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (30-100+ years)
				
